<body>

  <p class=3D"mediumtext">
    <span class=3D"maintitle">flat assembler</span><br>Documentation and tu=
torials.
  </p>

  <div class=3D"container">
   =20
<p class=3D"largetext">
This section provides browsable versions of the manuals and other documenta=
tion included in the flat assembler packages, as well as few other relevant=
 texts.
If you are looking for basic tutorials for assembly language, please visit =
the official <a href=3D"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCs_OWSjmFntZqjzSpg=
JoBhA">video channel</a> and <a href=3D"https://board.flatassembler.net/for=
um.php?f=3D23">our forums</a>.
</p>

<p class=3D"largetext">
First, a few documents concerning the new flat assembler g engine.
</p>

<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 85%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Dfasmg">flat assembler g<br>Introduction and Overview</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 08 Jun 2025</span><br>
    </td>
    <td>
      An introduction to flat assembler g that shows the intended purpose o=
f this engine and demonstrates
      how to construct an assembler for a given CPU architecture through ma=
croinstructions.
   </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Dfasmg_manual">flat assembler g<br>User Manual</a><br>
      <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 20 Mar 2026</span><br>
    </td>
    <td>
      The detailed description of the syntax of flat assembler g.
      This is a reference document that can also be read as a progressive g=
uide.
    </td>
  </tr>

</tbody></table>
</div>

<p class=3D"largetext">
The remaining documents are about the original flat assembler.
</p>

<div class=3D"links">
<table style=3D"width: 85%;">

  <colgroup>
    <col style=3D"width: 40%; max-width: 275px;">
    <col>
  </colgroup>

  <tbody><tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Dmanual">flat assembler 1.73<br>Programmer's Manual</a><br>
       <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 04 Jan 2022</span>
    </td>
    <td>
      This is the HTML version of documentation which is provided with all =
the flat assembler 1 packages.
      It contains an overview of the syntax and lists all the supported ins=
tructions and directives, with some
      elementary examples of usage. Reading this document is particularly r=
ecommended when you are experienced
      assembly language programmer but you are not familiar with the syntax=
 of flat assembler.
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Dwin32">Windows programming</a><br>
       <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 19 Apr 2016</span>
    </td>
    <td>
      This is the documentation for the standard set of includes that comes=
 with the flat assembler 1 for Windows package.
      It focuses on documenting the macroinstructions provided by this pack=
age, which are designed to simplify writing programs for this
      operating system, and also to emulate the syntax structures commonly =
used by other assemblers for this environment.
   </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Dufasm">Understanding<br>the flat assembler</a><br>
       <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 06 Apr 2016</span>
    </td>
    <td>
      This is an advanced guide to the various layers of flat assembler 1,
      it shows and explains some of the tricks you can do, however
      its main aim is to explain the interactions between different feature=
s of
      of assembler and preprocessor, which may be sometimes confusing unles=
s you understand
      what exactly is happening there.
    </td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>
      <a class=3D"boldlink" href=3D"https://flatassembler.net/docs.php?arti=
cle=3Ddesign">Design Principles</a><br>
       <span class=3D"smalltext">last update: 09 Feb 2009</span>
    </td>
    <td>
      An old overview of the principles that affected the design of flat as=
sembler 1.
      This text was written to help understand why it followed some differe=
nt choices than the other assemblers,
      for what main purposes it was initially designed and in what directio=
ns can it evolve.
    </td>
  </tr>

